True, you can and should allocate different amounts of VRAM for different sizes of actor. But you have to allocate the largest amount of memory that each actor can use. Otherwise, you get problems when all actors happen to switch to a larger cel at once.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Sep 17, 2014 9:24 pm</p><hr />
