That's a lot more complexity than just statically allocating a VRAM slot to each actor the way I do in <a href="https://pineight.com/gba/managing-sprite-vram.txt" class="postlink">my white paper about the technique on GBA</a>. Obviously it has to be slightly modified because you can rewrite only about a third of the sprite cels during one NTSC vblank, but averaging 20 fps across all sprites on screen still isn't half bad.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Sep 16, 2014 7:25 pm</p><hr />
